
[1]substantive

   SUB'STANTIVE, a. Betokening existence; as the substantive verb.

   1. Solid; depending on itself. [Not in use.]

    SUB'STANTIVE, n. In grammar, a noun or name; the part of speech which
    expresses something that exists, either material or immaterial. Thus
      man, horse, city, goodness, excellence, are substantives. [Better
        called name, L. nomen, or even noun, a corruption of nomen.]
